title: Retail price for granulated sugar in the U.S. 2000 to 2017
yAxis: Price per pound in U.S. cents
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Price per pound in U.S. cents, containing a total of 18 data points.
Overall Price per pound in U.S. cents has increased over the Year.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2005 and 2006.
Maximum Price per pound in U.S. cents, about 69.41 was reported at Year 2012
The lowest Price per pound in U.S. cents, of value 42.41 was reported at Year 2000
